name: The Nest Rooftop Bar At Thompson Seattle

address.streetAddress: 110 Stewart Street  Rooftop Of Thompson Seattle

name: East Ballard Breweries Tours
description:
TOUR INCLUDES, REUBEN'S BREWS, WHEELIE POP BREWING, AND LUCKY ENVELOPE BREWING

In the neighborhood brewing visionaries brewed the first barrel of Redhook Ale back in 1983 and started a craft brewing revolution. That revolution continues now with the highest concentration of craft breweries in the world. How this happened is part of the story that has made Seattle, and Ballard, the world's premier craft brewing center. We will explore this history, the history of beer and learn about different beer styles. We will learn what to look for when tasting new beers and appreciate the many historic and contemporary styles.

At each brewery our Cicerone certified Beer Guide will lead a guided tasting of four, 4-once beers, for a total of 12 different beers. This is about 3 pints of beer. 
* 3/4 of a mile, 1,500 steps
* Each guide a certified cicerone
* 12 different 4 oz beers
* Free 4-oz souvenir tasting glass
* Free souvenir Bottle Key-Chain opener
* Beer & Food Pairing Guide

review.name: Best Beer Tasting Experience Ever!
review.reviewBody: Tim is a wonderful guide and very knowledgeable about beer brewing. I learned so much from him from the use of ingredients to how conditions of brewing turn out the various kinds of beer. He is friendly and easy to talk to. His selection of breweries and beers from each brewery were excellent. His appreciation of brewery owners who operate their business with a healthy socially responsibility is inspiring.  I absolutely enjoyed the experience and highly recommend this to both beer lovers and causal drinkers!!!

name: Old Ballard Brewery Tour
description:
TOUR INCLUDES REUBEN'S BREW, WHEELIE POP BREWING, AND LAGUNITAS TAPROOM AND BEER SANCTUARY. 

Our tour ends just a few short blocks from Old Ballard's Historic District where you can find over two dozen restaurants, pubs, and cocktail lounges. We'll sample traditional, old-world brewing styles and new, experimental beers that you will find only in these breweries. We will learn why the close proximity of Northwest barley fields, the most productive hops growing region in the world and visionary brewing pioneers have made Seattle the center of the craft brewing renaissance.

At each brewery our Cicerone certified Beer Guide will lead a guided tasting of four, 4-once beers, for a total of 12 different beers. This is about 3 pints of beer. 
* Just over half a mile, 1,260 steps
* Each guide a certified cicerone
* 12 different 4 oz beers
* Free 4-oz souvenir tasting glass
* Free souvenir Bottle Key-Chain opener
* Beer & Food Pairing Guide

review.name: Fabulous Brewery Tour
review.reviewBody: My tour guide was incredible! He was very thorough and precise. Three different breweries and experiences. Amazing beer and company!

review.name: Enjoyable
review.reviewBody: Learning about the history of beer and Seattle. Didn’t realize that Americans were such prudes about alcohol

review.name: Walking Brewery Tour in Ballard
review.reviewBody: Tim was our tour guide.  He has a wealth of information about the history of beer.  He also explained, clearly, the differences between lagers and ales.  As we tasted through 12 beers at 3 breweries, he was able to help us appreciate the nuances of taste.  And, it was October's, so the beers being served were not his "regular" beers.  Just an excellent experience.

review.name: Stay Hoppy
review.reviewBody: Wow we learned a lot about the history of brewing and current breweries in Seattle. Our tour guide was amazing as well!

review.name: Best tour of our visit!
review.reviewBody: Very informative and friendly. We were treated like old friends and gently encouraged to try beer outside our comfort zones. It worked!

review.name: Amazing brewery tour
review.reviewBody:
Our tour was amazing. Tim, our tour guide, was great! He was the friendliest guy and definitely knew his stuff. I learned so much about craft beer!

Definitely a great experience.

review.name: Really knowledgeable beer guide.
review.reviewBody: Tim was a great guide for 3 breweries.  Highly recommend you taking this tour while in Seattle. .....

review.name: Great information and a lot of great beer
review.reviewBody: We had a great time on this tour. Our guide was super knowledgeable about the area of town we were in, the beer we were drinking, and you could tell he was very passionate about his town and beer. Our group of 6 had a wonderful time and would definitely do the tour again.

review.name: Great Variety and Education
review.reviewBody: My wife and I took the tour, and had a great time!  Tim was very informative and we were able to taste a variety of beers, while learning about the brewing process.  I was amazing to see the different breweries and each had their own unique vibe.  We really enjoyed it! I highly recommend it!

review.name: Ales and Tales
review.reviewBody: Tim Lorang was our guide for this tour. It was just four of us on this tour, my husband and myself, and another couple. Tim was a great guide. He had lots of stories and tons of information about the beer business and beer itself. We started at the Lagunitas tap room and went on to NWPeak and ended at Peddler Brewing Company. We tasted a surprisingly wide variety of beers in these three places. Lagers, IPAs, sours, stouts, we tasted them all. We learnt about different stages of brewing, the effects of adding hops at different stages of the brewing process, the difference in taste depending on the degree of barley roasting and so on. I would recommend this tour highly. It’s a fun outing, you hang out with a fun guide, you learn a lot about beer and seattle’s microbrewery scene, AND you get to drink great beer! What’s not to love, eh?

name: Fishermen's Terminal Brewery Tour
description:
TOUR INCLUDES FIGUREHEAD BREWING, the FIDHERMEN'S TERMINAL AND ROOFTOP BREW COMPANY. On the south shore of Salmon Bay, beneath the Ballard Bridge, and north of the BSNF train yards is Seattle's historic Fishermen's Terminal and the home port for the North Pacific Fishing Fleet. Think of the Discovery Channel’s Deadliest Catch and you will know exactly what kind of intrepid fishermen sail from this port. Luckily for them, and for us, there are two great breweries on either side of the port, and we are going to taste six great beers at each.
At each brewery our Cicerone certified Beer Guide will lead a guided tasting of six, 4-once beers, for a total of 12 different beers. This is about 3 pints of beer. 
* 3/4 of a mile, 1,500 steps
* Each guide a certified cicerone
* 12 different 4 oz beers
* Free 4-oz souvenir tasting glass
* Free souvenir Bottle Key-Chain opener
* Beer & Food Pairing Guide

review.name: Walking tour
review.reviewBody: Tom was very knowledgeable and was very easy going the tour was very informative and the beer  history was top notch

review.name: Great tour and great beer!
review.reviewBody: This was a very informative beer tasting and tour! We are beer "enthusiasts" but by no means are we experts. Our tour guide was very informative, fun, and had a ton of stories and knowledge to share. The walk between breweries was short and gave us a chance to drink some water! LOL

review.name: History in the beer making
review.reviewBody: If you’re looking for a great brewery tour with a knowledgeable guide that will take you to the sweet local breweries at Fisherman’s Terminal, look no further than here. Our guide Tim, a certified cicerone and local gave the knowledge and history we needed to thoroughly enjoy each beer. From saison to stout to Ipa to session and everything in between we were able to walk away humbled with a little bit of knowledge of the complexity that beer has to offer. Most importantly, Tim gave a history lesson  of Seattle that is able to give locals and visitors an appreciation for this wonderful city. Thank you for an amazing experience!!!

review.name: Great Beer Great Guide
review.reviewBody: Tim was such a fantastic guide!  Not only did I enjoy the majority of the beer on this tour, but the experience was elevated by Tim's knowledge and stories.  I thought I knew a lot about beer going into this tour and was really just looking forward to drinking.  I was blown away by the entertaining information that Tim provided.  I would definitely do this tour again!

review.name: Very Enjoyable!!
review.reviewBody: Recently when visiting Seattle my husband, cousins and I decided to go on a brewery tour. The only date that worked for us was a Monday, and Seattle Brewery Walking Tours (SBWT) worked with us and we were able to go on the Fisherman's Terminal Tour. SBWT is headed up by a man named Tim, and he leads all of the tours. We met at Urban Family Brewing, and Tim gave us bags with taster glasses and papers with useful beer-related info. Tim went in and got us each a flight of 4 beers, and we worked our way through tasting each one and talking a bit about the history of each type of beer as well as the history of the brewery. At Figurehead Brewery, we were able to see some of the equipment and ingredients used in the beer making process, and at Rooftop bar, we met the owner and spoke with him about how he got started. Tim is pleasant, easy to talk to, and very knowledgable about beer. He seems to have a good rapport with the breweries and gives a great tour! We tasted 4 beers at each venue and it took 3-4 hrs. Very Enjoyable!

review.name: Highly Recommended!
review.reviewBody:
Wow, what a great tour. Tim expertly guided us through over 25 beers, their style, origin and unique flavours profiles. 

If you’re interested in all things beer and enjoy great story telling then this tour is a must do when you’re in Seattle!

review.name: Wonderful tour guide, great beer!
review.reviewBody: Tim was SO much fun; he is a great tour guide and provided a lot of beer resources. Yes, you can visit these breweries on your own, but Tim has great relationships with the people and got us extra tasters and interesting chat about the breweries and beers. The breweries themselves are excellent and all within a short walk of each other. They all brew very different styles and there is something for everyone on this tour. We highly recommend the tour; you don't need a bus!

name: Central Ballard Brewery Tour
description:
TOUR INCLUDES URBAN FAMILY BREWING, STOUP BREWING, AND OBEC BREWING. 

In the center of Ballard's Brewing District, these three breweries stand out. At each guided tasting we will learn about the different beer styles, what to look for when you are tasting beer, the history of beer, and the craft brewing renaissance in the Pacific Northwest. For example, we'll learn how an obscure export ale for British soldiers was reborn in the Pacific Northwest to become the most popular craft beer style in North America or how a small Czech town gave its name to one of the world's most popular beer styles.

At each brewery our Cicerone certified Beer Guide will lead a guided tasting of four, 4-once beers, for a total of 12 different beers. This is about 3 pints of beer. 
* 3/4 of a mile, 1,500 steps
* Each guide a certified cicerone
* 12 different 4 oz beers
* Free 4-oz souvenir tasting glass
* Free souvenir Bottle Key-Chain opener
* Beer & Food Pairing Guide

review.name: Fun exploration of Seattle's microbrewery culture
review.reviewBody:
What a great introduction to the microbrewery culture of the Pacific Northwest! Tim, who runs this tour, is very passionate and extremely knowledgeable about beer. He even created a beer guide, including an explanation of beer terminology, tasting sheets, and a pairing guide for participants. 
Most of all tho, the tour was a lot of fun. The breweries all seemed very popular with locals and we had a total of 3 flights with 4 small beers on each of them. Needles to say, I couldn't finish all of them - but I definitely had fun trying. As someone who isn't a beer expert at all, I really feel I learned a lot about the different brewing methods and my own taste on this tour. 
Tim is a wonderful guide (our small group had a little meetup hiccup in the beginning which he managed smoothly) and I fully recommend taking this tour to learn more about Seattle's beer culture.

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody: Absolutely brilliant tour and can’t recommend this highly enough. Our guide was perfect- he was knowledgeable funny and very entertaining. He made us all feel welcome and built a great rapport with the group. This was much more enjoyable than I expected. Do it!

review.name: Lots of fun
review.reviewBody: Tim was a wonderful tour guide.  He was knowledgable and funny.  We tasted many beers and the pours were all substantial.  We visited 3 breweries on our tour.  Ballard is a great area for craft breweries.

review.name: A hoppin great time
review.reviewBody: Very knowledgeable beer guide. We had a wonderful experience at each brewery. Would definitely recommend it to a friend.

review.name: Book this!
review.reviewBody: Tim was awesome!  He starts by talking about how to best sample each beer (observe, smell, taste, feel), but as we drank each type, he’d talk about the history and origin story.  Tim was a cornucopia of knowledge, both brewing and general history of Seattle.  After a short while, it felt more like hanging with a knowledgeable friend than a “tour”.  Highly recommend him!!

review.name: Fun times
review.reviewBody: Tim was knowledgeable patient and friendly.  He made you step out of your comfort zone. Which in turn makes you learn more about what you like and don't like.

review.name: Fun, Informative, and Entertaining Tour
review.reviewBody:
I’m so happy we signed up.  Tim is friendly, knowledgeable, and passionate about beer.  My husband and I loved the experience and appreciated that Tim did the tour even though it was just us two who signed up. 
For the first two breweries, we sat outside.  The last one was inside, and the brewery had its giant door open.

review.name: Ballard Brew Tours - Seattle walking tours.      August 2021 -  Tim guide
review.reviewBody:
Tim was an amazing guide, passionate about the Ballard brew scene, and very  knowledgeable about the history of beer. 
I highly recommend his tours !
Five  plus stars!!!

review.name: Fun beer tastings and tour
review.reviewBody: My husband and I had a great time with Tim on the Central Ballard brewery tour on the 4th of July. We learned SO much about beer and experienced an incredibly wide variety of tasting. Tim keeps his tours small so you can expect a lot of attention and Q&A opportunities. Most of the breweries don't have food so maybe bring some like snacks (nuts or pretzels) or have a solid meal before you go. It is a pretty good amount of beer and the "tastings" are pretty hardy. I would definitely recommend any of the tours to beers lovers, or even just beer likers, as everyone is bound to find a beer that suits their tastes :)  I look forward to taking another tour with Tim on our next visit to Seattle.

review.name: Tim is fantastic company, deeply interesting and funny
review.reviewBody: I really faffed up and we were an HOUR late. Despite this Tim made it work. He is FASCINATING and very funny. I am really looking forward to doing another of his tours but in a different area. We had a tremendously fun evening and I strongly recommend Tim to anyone who has even a vague interest in beer. Also afterwards we had the option of hanging about with him and his lovely wife but we had to head home back to the dogs-which in hindsight we could have brought with us.

itemListElement.name: Ultimate Mt. Rainier Tour from Seattle: Helicopter Flight & Alpine Hike

name: Ultimate Mt. Rainier Tour from Seattle: Helicopter Flight & Alpine Hike
description:
This full-day tour is the best way to see the most of Mt. Rainier in a single day: combine an epic helicopter flight across this rugged landscape with a guided alpine hike. Take the most “scenic route” possible on a 35-minute flight between Seattle and Mt. Rainier. On the ground at Mt. Rainier, your naturalist guide will walk you through alpine terrain that you glimpsed from the air. Enjoy a delicious catered picnic lunch before returning to Seattle. Put this trip of a lifetime on your bucket list!

-Fly between Seattle & Mt. Rainier on an exclusive helicopter flight
-Stroll through stunning sub-alpine terrain above 6,000’, coming face-to-face with Mt. Rainier’s largest glaciers.
-Boutique excursion limited to just up to 6 guests. 
-Take incredible bird’s-eye view photos of the wild landscape below you.
-A delicious picnic lunch surrounded by nature awaits you. 
-Join the only tour company to offer this exclusive combo experience.

review.name: Mt. Ranier Helicopter tour and hiking
review.reviewBody: This was an amazing tour! Definitely one of the best trips I've taken in Seattle. The helicopter ride was exhilarating and educational. The hike was awesome with a very knowledgeable tour guide. The catered lunch was much more than I expected. The guides were in no hurry and made the experience worth every dime spent.

review.name: Great for locals and visitors!
review.reviewBody: This is probably the best day trip in Seattle. Michael was a fantastic tour guide, lunch was delicious, and the helicopter ride was everything we hoped for and more. Loads of fun for a couples and groups alike.

review.name: Wonderful local adventure!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I are locals in Seattle. Because of COVID we’ve been unable to travel this summer. We took this tour as a way to have a wonderful local adventure. The guides Michael and Whitney were knowledgeable and showed us some really amazing things. July was a perfect time to be in the mountains because the wildflowers were in bloom. Our tour culminated in a helicopter ride back to Seattle. It was a highly recommended experience, especially if you’re local and want to “get away”.

review.name: Mount Rainier Helicopter and hiking tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour! The views were spectacular, weather was perfect, and Michael our guide was awesome - very knowledgeable, great conversation. It was a blast flying with Matt! The hike was just right, lunch was delicious, We recommend this highly!

review.name: Vacations
review.reviewBody: This was a very good experience with my family. Michael the guide was so nice and patient with us. I highly recommend this tour because you can see all type of landscape. Take good pictures. The picnic food was very good.

itemListElement.name: Private Mt. Rainier Helicopter Flight & Alpine Hike from Seattle

review.name: One of the best days ever!
review.reviewBody: One of those days you will never forget. My friends and I were amazed for 6 hours straight. I was not sure whether to take pictures or just keep looking. The food was great, the guide, the pilot were super nice, the hike was not hard, the air was fresh. We chose the option to travel both ways in the helicopter, absolutely recommended!

itemListElement.name: Chef Guided Food Tour of Pike Place Market- 1 Hour

name: Chef Guided Food Tour of Pike Place Market- 1 Hour
description:
An abbreviated version of our 2 hour tour, this chef-guided, small-group food tour takes a journey through Pacific Northwest culture by tasting Seattle’s best artisan vendors in the famous Pike Place Market. Get the inside scoop on where chefs shop and where locals hang out. Enjoy diverse tastings at 4 different places — and food options like mocha, yogurt, chowder and more. All groups are kept to 11 people to ensure easier navigation of the market, more tastings, and a better platform to ask questions and interact with the group. Leave with a 10% discount card to shop at all of our partners. 
This tour is just a small taste of the market and does not constitute a full meal.
This tour does require a medium physical ability to navigate the market.

review.name: Good food, Good times, Great Experience!  Thanks Chef Sean!
review.reviewBody: This was such a delightful experience with Chef Sean!  We made several stops in Pike Place Market, trying delicious foods and learning the history of the Market as well.  I & my kids both enjoyed the tour, and highly recommend it.  The tips for getting food more quickly from the chowder restaurant was nice, as well as the history on some of the shops.  Later, Sean even gave us some tips on restaurants outside the Market to try for other meals.  Thanks!

review.name: Don't miss this Tour! Best chef guide and great food!
review.reviewBody: Chef John was fantastic! He was very considerate of everyone's needs. He was very knowledgeable about the market and the city. The food we sampled was amazing. It was great to have John along to skip all the very long longs to get our samples. It was a great variety of items to sample and it was fun to learn the history of the market. This was by far our favorite tour we did in Seattle. I highly recommend it to everyone.

review.name: Amazing Girls Day Out Experience
review.reviewBody: Amazing tour! Our guide, Carolyn, was the best!! We loved all her added information! We would highly recommend this company and our guide to any of our family and friends!! Great day out at the market!!

review.name: Best tasting tour with awesome tour guide
review.reviewBody: Chef John was fantastic! Lots of great info, very charismatic and lots of great conversation. Great tour guide, didn’t rush us through the tour, and we had plenty of small tastings in an hour. Definitely would recommend!

review.name: Good food and fun history!
review.reviewBody: Chef John has a lot of energy and the experience is a lot of fun. Good food and fun history! Highly recommend.

review.name: Must Do Foodie Experience In Seattle
review.reviewBody: Please see our review under Eat Seattle Restaurant which is the provider of this tour.  Chef Eric O. is personable, knowledgeable, and went out of his way to accomodate our very tight schedule.

name: Hard Rock Cafe Seattle
description: Rock your senses with a prix-fixe menu at the Seattle Hard Rock Cafe. Classic American cooking comes to the heart of the Emerald City, where you’ll enjoy a 2- or 3-course meal with your choice of theme. Each option comes with a drink (coffee, tea or soda) and dessert. Expect entrees like the classic cheeseburger, a half-rack of hickory-smoked ribs, salmon, steak and even some vegetarian options. Love All - Serve All!

review.name: Hard Rock Experience
review.reviewBody:
We have visited Hard Rock Cafes around the world.  We always stop in the local one to buy our pin and have a snack.  This Hard Rock was not busy and had this ‘menacing’ sign that 22% surcharge would be charged to every order.  When they sat us at our table they asked if we were OK with the surcharge.  There was a family of 4 behind us literally having an argument they would not come in because of the surcharge poster.  

We just ordered a couple of local brews and some nachos to share.  The Nachos were soggy.  Our waitress was extremely peppy and helpful.  We asked her if she would get any of the 22% surcharge so we would know how to tip for her good service.  She said the staff gets 17% of that 22% surcharge and the rest goes to Hard Rock.  Personally, I think the uninformative messaging about the surcharge deters business.

review.name: Poor experience.
review.reviewBody:
Not the great buzzy atmosphere that I associate with the Hard Rock Cafe but we were on holiday and hungry and I expected that it would make up for it with food and service. Our waitress was fine and the order for food and drink taken promptly. Drinks arrived ok and we waited for food. I had the Salmon on a plank and it was served at the same time as my partners salad for their chicken and beef fajitas but the chicken and beef didn’t turn up, it was serviced by a different waiter who said the rest was on its way. I started my food but ate slowly so my partner could join but even so I had nearly finished when theirs turned up, again delivered by a different waiter. The food was decent but it is not acceptable to serve the meal separately the way it was. I did not leave any tip when I paid the bill but I did give the waitress a small cash tip as she had been done a good job and explained to her why I wasn’t tipping anyone else.
I will not go there again and will think twice now about going to any other branch.

review.name: Overpriced mediocre food
review.reviewBody:
On arrival we were not told of the compulsory 22% gratuity as reported by previous reviews. The greater was not cheerful or inviting- quite the opposite. We opted for the roof terrace - the server was ok although we requested our starters and mains didn’t come out at the same time as recent previous USA restaurants did - we were assured this wouldn’t happen, but it did. Nacho starter a little on the cold side, but loaded really well. We sent back the mains as we were still eating the nachos. Mains came back out and were cooked well. Food on the whole cooked well. And I opted to only pay 10% gratuity which is all I felt was deserved. 
We went to the rock store and no pint glasses - we have been to 58 Hard Rock Cafe’s over the world and have a pint glass from each - this store had none and the server was nonplussed that they had none - really poor. But actually we blame the owners of the franchise’s  more -  they are no longer interested in the principle of Hard Rock Cafe just how much money they can make from the hotels and casinos- destroying everything established by the original Hard Rock Cafe in London. We used to track hard rock cafes across the world but we will be not any more. In future we will pop in for a drink to say we have visited but I won’t be paying for over priced mediocre food.

review.name: Didn't make it past the host
review.reviewBody:
The host told us there was a mandatory 22% gratuity when we walked in the door - I asked if it was going to be a 22% worthy service and the host looked blankly at me and just shrugged. We turned around and got out of there. Was also suspicious that it was half empty at 8pm on an otherwise very busy Saturday night
.

review.name: This one is bad
review.reviewBody: A 22% enforced gratuity is fine for good food and good service of which we had neither. I asked for a simple straw and got it AFTER my meal. My burger was woefully undercooked. My daughters pasta marinara was a reheated dish with rubbery pasta. I am done with the Hard Rock franchise.

review.name: Enforced Gratuity
review.reviewBody:
Before we even sat down for a lunch during All-Star weekend, I pondered the question as to why the restaurant was so empty yet the market place area was packed with people.
Then I learned from the hosted before we we were seated that there will be a 22% enforced gratuity to our bill.  When I looked at the menu and the average price of a meal was around $20+ and with a party of four before any drinks would put the average bill over $90.  At 22%, that’s up to $20 gratuity before you even see your server.  
I believe in the tipping system starting at 18% and go up from there but to enforce a 22% coming from an institution like the Hard Rock Café will leave a horrible taste in your mouth.
I’ve visited over 50 Hard Rock Café’s over my time and this experience may have put an end to it.

review.name: Awful
review.reviewBody: Really, really, bad. Got seated and forgot about. Hostess eventually apologized but then we were no longer forgotten but ignored again. Service was beyond awful, then to top it off, food was also pretty bad. Fries & kids meal were ok (came out way before adult meals which was nice but then adult meals took so long to come)  but chicken sandwiches super dry. The server literally went out of his way to not come by, We had to flag him down anytime we needed something and each time he said he would be back and never came back.  Someone else brought out food thankfully or we prob never would have gotten any. it was not good.  We never got drink refills, and drinks were gone well before food arrived. Server flagged down and said he would bring but they never came. The place was not busy, lunch took so long my son went to sleep. We really shouldn't have paid, it as that bad but we had to go to the airport and we had been there so long we wanted to GTFO.  This place was so bad it has become an ongoing family joke. "At least its not the Hard Rock Seattle," & "cant be as bad as Hard Rock,Seattle."  I'd say anyone could have a bad day, but not a single employee seemed to notice or care how bad it was so might just be their norm. I'd avoid.

review.name: Yummy
review.reviewBody: Stopped for lunch while at Pike Place Market.  No wait and server (Brittany) was great.  Food was tasty and served promptly.  They do add 22% gratuity to every check and it's taxable.  It wasn't a surprise and there was a sign right at the hostess station and the hostess also verbally informed us and asked if we were ok with it.

review.name: Don't bother going.
review.reviewBody: I had the pulled pork sandwich, and my friend had nachos. They both were awful.  I've always wanted to go, finally when I do it a horrible experience.

review.name: John is awsome
review.reviewBody: We have been into this location several times. The food and service are always great. Our server has been John the last few times and he is THE BEST! Always friendly, makes recommendations and knows the area. Best server in Seattle if you ask us!

itemListElement.name: Make Jewelry from Your Watercolor Painting

name: Make Jewelry from Your Watercolor Painting
description:
This is a perfect project for beginners and experienced artists. With my low-risk and high success process, you will create a necklace you love regardless of experience. 

We will cover basic watercolor techniques, composition, color schemes and developing trust in your creative wisdom. In my relaxed and comfortable studio, we will play with professional quality watercolor and materials to tap your intuition and creativity while exploring shapes and possibility. 

The majority of time will focus on painting with lots of times for experimenting, one-on-one guidance, questions, and answers. You will have the opportunity to try different ideas and designs before picking the one that you like the best. Like my necklaces, your pendant(s) will be unique to you. 

You will surprise yourself with what you can do!

itemListElement.name: Skagit Valley Birding + Deception Pass Day Tour From Seattle

name: Skagit Valley Birding + Deception Pass Day Tour From Seattle
description:
No two tours with Evergreen Escapes are the same! Our guides craft itineraries that reflect the best of what the Park has to offer that day, including group interests and dynamics. Please note that the itinerary outlined is a SAMPLE of potential destinations that could be included in the tour.

Our Deception Pass State Park Tour from Seattle is an excellent way to spend a day outside of the city. Located on the northern end of the largest island in the Salish Sea, Deception Pass provides unparalleled opportunities to experience the true Pacific Northwest with miles of rugged coast, massive old growth trees, and adrenaline pumping bridges. 

This small-group day trip limited to 10 people includes French-pressed coffee & tea, pastries, light snacks, a picnic-style lunch and downtown Seattle pick-up and drop-off. Don't worry about a thing.

review.name: Excellent tour!!!
review.reviewBody: My daughter, her partner, and I thoroughly enjoyed our excursion with Matthew Card. The hike was great, and Matthew even brought walking sticks, snacks, drinks, and a picnic lunch for our group of 9 on this trip. Matthew brought binoculars for the whale-watching tour at Anacortes also—many thanks! I was using his binoculars when four Orcas decided to breach. Wonderful tour, wonderful tour guide. Highly recommend!

review.name: This Winter Experience is a Must!
review.reviewBody: I took a mid winter trip to Seattle and had a free day to do something outside the city. I chose this tour because I liked the balance between outdoor experiences in the Skagit Valley and Deception Pass and the history aspects at the military fort and local farms. We were able to see so many birds at the first stop - large white swans in the hundreds- took a beautiful morning hike along a trail at the park, and enjoyed some delicious fruit wines at the last stop. We had Dan as our guide, who was so knowledgeable about everything we were seeing, especially all the birds(!!) and really made this experience a day we will never forget.  My friends and I really enjoyed exploring the old fort where you can wander through all of the bunkers, it really takes you back in time!  I would recommend this tour for anyone looking for a fun outing from Seattle with a little bit of hiking, a little bit of history, a little bit of wildlife sightings and a lot of amazing views! Thanks Dan and Evergreen Escapes for an amazing day trip!

name: Experience Seattle Small-Group Tour
description:
In creating this Seattle tour for 2018, we set out to make the tour our guides want to go on with friends. We made a tour that keeps people outside, touches many of the highlights and hidden facets of Seattle that make it…well, Seattle, and we make sure that we eat and drink well all day!  This small-group day trip limited to 10 people includes French-pressed coffee & tea, pastries, light snacks, local wine tasting and downtown Seattle hotel transport by luxury vehicle.

Lunch is on our own--but only because we visit the famous Ballard Farmer's Market and travelers like to try many different cuisines and options!

name: Seattle-Tacoma International Airport Hotel Shuttle
description: If Your Flying Into or Out Of The City, Allow The Chiefton Group To Meet You There or Get You There… Get Curbside Pick Up / Drop Off Service. Enjoy The Scenic Ride From and/or The Scenic Ride Back to The Airport.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Night Tour with a Local Guide, Private & Custom

name: Seattle Night Tour with a Local Guide, Private & Custom
description:
On this personalised experience discover the nightlife in Seattle's hip Capitol Hill neighbourhood. Locals know how to enjoy a craft beer and shake a cocktail or two, so why not swap an espresso for an espresso martini? 
Your Host will introduce the best of Seattle’s bar culture, hippest clubs, classic dive bars or independent music venues to you.. You'll try some killer cocktails in prohibition-era style speakeasies, explore hipster craft breweries and discover classy wine bars.
This character-packed neighbourhood is proud of its vibrant nightlife scene and is the only place to be after dark - the real Seattle after the sun goes down! 

Our handpicked hosts are culinary connoisseurs and history buffs, bakers and bankers, students and seniors. Like the people who travel with us, they have different backgrounds and interests – but they’re all so passionate about the place they call home, they choose to spend their free time sharing it with the like-minded travelers matched to them.

name: Seattle Holidays Lights & Lore Tour
description: Unlock the magic of the season with Tours Northwest on our 2-hour Seattle Holiday Lights & Lore Tour! Learn the history behind your favorite holiday traditions while we make our way through local Seattle neighborhoods, showing off the best bright lights in the city. Grab a hot cocoa before jumping on board our warm, festive mini coach and let your guide show off the holiday spirit of downtown Seattle, Candy Cane Lane and more on this 2-hour tour.
